{"type":"message","id":"1421af73","parentId":"b2960ed7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:04:47.829Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gztzneepg2cs_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 020317\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: TIC (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSince this is a new session (pulse_2026-03-24 020102.md is the last pulse), and I need to implement the TIC experiment, I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script or implement it in a way that can process the pulse logs\r\n2. Define what \"invariant\" vs \"variant\" means in the context of pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and understand their structure, then create a TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to understand the structure of the pulse logs. Let me create a TIC experiment implementation. The key insight is that causal structure = invariant structure. So I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Parse pulse logs\r\n2. Identify patterns that persist across pulses (invariants) vs patterns that change\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script or Python script that:\r\n1. Reads all pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features/markers that are consistent (invariants) vs changing (variants)\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete implementation. I'll create `research/tic_experiment.ps1` that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions, there's also:\r\n\r\n\r\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n\r\nI'll focus on the TIC classifier as the primary task. I need to design a script that can analyze pulse logs and extract meaningful patterns. The script will involve parsing log files, identifying consistent and changing elements, and developing a prediction mechanism based on these observations.\r\n\r\nThe implementation will require careful parsing of log structures, feature extraction, and a probabilistic approach to predicting subsequent pulse content. I'll start by creating a basic framework that can handle log analysis and pattern recognition.\r\n\r\nMy next step involves examining the current log format to ensure compatibility with the new TIC experiment script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants vs variants in pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as invariant (causal structure) vs variant, then tests next-pulse prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinInvariantCount = 3,      # Min occurrences to classify as invariant\r\n    [double]$InvariantThreshold = 0.7  # 70%+ occurrence rate = invariant\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSScriptRoot -Parent) -Parent\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$logFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \"$ProjectRoot/logs\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\nif ($logFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[TIC] ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($logFiles.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Analyzing $($logFiles.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract feature markers from each pulse\r\nfunction Get-PulseFeatures {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{\r\n        GoalsUpdated = $Content -match \"Last updated: (\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})\"\r\n        PhaseComplete = $Content -match \"Phase \\d+ COMPLETE\"\r\n        PendingItems = ($Content | Select-String -Pattern \"^\\s*-\\s*\\[\").Matches.Count\r\n        MutationApplied = $Content -match \"### MUTATION\" -and $Content -notmatch \"No mutations applied\"\r\n        HasObservation = $Content -match \"### OBSERVATION\"\r\n        HasAction = $Content -match \"### ACTION\"\r\n        CompressionMentioned = $Content -match \"compress|invariant|causal\"\r\n        GapMentioned = $Content -match \"gap|decay|discontinuity\"\r\n        ArchitectureMentioned = $Content -match \"architecture|TemporalAttention|Infant\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Collect features across all pulses\r\n$pulseData = @()\r\n$allFeatures = @{}\r\n\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $logFiles.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $logFiles[$i].FullName -Raw\r\n    $features = Get-PulseFeatures $content\r\n    \r\n    $pulseData += @{\r\n        Index = $i\r\n        File = $logFiles[$i].Name\r\n        Features = $features\r\n        Content = $content\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($key in $features.Keys) {\r\n        if (-not $allFeatures.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $allFeatures[$key] = @()\r\n        }\r\n        $allFeatures[$key] += $features.$key\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify features as invariant\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:03:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332287828}}
